cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

The paper is about scene parsing, which is a computer vision task, so it is likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) category. The paper proposes a new type of recurrent neural network (RNN) for scene labeling, which involves learning long-range dependencies among image units. This suggests that the paper could also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) category, as RNNs are a type of machine learning model. Additionally, the paper introduces an attention model to select relevant dependencies, which is a common technique in natural language processing (NLP) and could place the paper in the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.CL (Computation and Language) categories. Finally, the paper's use of dense connections between image units could also be relevant to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) category, which covers topics related to neural networks and their applications.
